items.content_text: Sawfly (perga spp.) Two possibility: Perga affinis or Perga dorsalis. In "Pests, Diseases, Ailments and Allies of Australian Plants" book by David Jones (2015), page 284 and 285, Perga dorsalis is longer (up to 7cm) than Perga affinis (up to 4cm), and has prominent bristly white hairs.
